description:
Enrich your NYC experience with a cozy stay in this geek-chic inspired apartment in Sugar Hill! This 1 bedroom comfortably sleeps someone flying solo or a duo sharing a bed, but can accommodate a few extra guests in the living room on the queen size air mattress and fold-down sofa. Conveniently located near 5 different trains (A, C, B, D, 1) that get you to midtown within 30 minutes. It is also within walking distance of many fantastic modern restaurants, bars, coffee shops, and grocery stores!

The apartment has very high ceilings and a lot of natural light, making it a very comfortable and pleasant environment.

You will have access to the whole apartment.  You will enter the building on the ground floor, then just walk on up to the fourth floor!  It is a small, cozy, and quiet building with only two apartments per floor.

I can offer any sort of help you may require, but ideally will only see you when you check in or out.  I want you to have your space and enjoy yourself!

There are a lot of great restaurants, bars, and coffee shops nearby.  Some examples are Uptown Bourbon, Harlem Public, Monkey Cup, Taszo Espresso Bar, The Chipped Cup, and Tsion Cafe.  There are also a lot of fantastic food delivery options.  I recommend downloading the app "Seamless".

You will be near 5 different trains, the A, C, B, C, and 1.  The C is the local blue line and is only two blocks from the apartment.  The others are about an 8 minute walk away.
house_rules:
• Check in time is flexible
• May not be safe or suitable for children (0-12 years)
• No parties or events
• Not suitable for pets
• No smoking

- Must be careful and respectful of the space in general, but specifically the hand made, one of a kind art pieces. They are irreplaceable!
- Quiet hours after 10 PM
- Remove shoes after entering and leave them by the front door or in the shoe tree in the closet.

photos.caption: The living room, as seen from the kitchen.  Coffee table can be moved to make room for the air mattress, and the couch folds down flat as well to provide addition sleeping space.
A collapsible table and foldable chairs can be opened up to become a dining area,  seating 4 easily but could accommodate as many as 6.
Front door, with both a push lock on the handle and a deadbolt for extra security.
The front and bedroom doors as seen from the living room.
Hallway leading to bathroom, as seen from the front door.
Mounted shower head that can be removed to become hand held.
A view of the bar when it is not Christmastime.
Another view of the collapsible table in it's resting area, with one flap opened out.  The table is only about 15 inches deep when folded up fully against the wall.  The door is the coat closet.

review.comments: My stay in James's house was perfect! The apartment is very cozy and comfortable and it has everything you need. The subway stop is just a couple of blocks away and the neighborhood is very well communicated. James was very helpful and we had excellent communication. 100% recommended.
